-- Europe retail market for socially responsible investing up 18 pct
-- By Simon Jessop
-- Wed Oct 29, 2014 10:09AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 29 (Reuters) - The European retail market for funds focused on socially responsible investing grew 18 percent to 127 billion euros ($161.82 billion) in the 12 months to June 2014, a report on Wednesday showed.

The number of funds also rose, to 957 from 922 in the year earlier period, the report by Vigeo, which evaluates corporate responsibility, and fund analyst firm Morningstar said. The largest asset increases were in France, which added 7.6 billion euros, and the UK, with 3.1 billion euros, it said.